  <title translate="true">MT-POP-Motion Continuity</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Continuity</keyword><keyword translate="true">Motion Continuity</keyword><keyword translate="true">Motion Discontinuity</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2" style="width:450px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:200px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MT-Motion-Discontinuity.ipp" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[1,2,3-  Motion Discontinuity
4,5 - Motion Continuity]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Motion Discontinuity</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-2.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-3.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">:</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> defined by the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">lowest</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-POP-Motion-Derivative" styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">motion-derivative</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> in which there is an instantaneous step in the motion graph. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Motion-Continuity</text><image src="Red-14-4.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-5.gif" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: has </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">motion-continuity</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> when a </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">motion-derivative </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">does not have a step in its motion-graph, and in its lower motion-derivatives.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">For mechanical systems, it is important to make sure that the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Position</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Velocity</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, and </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> motion graphs have motion-continuity. This means Jerk will be finite at all times in its graph.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">For example, a motion has</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true"> </text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">an</text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true"> Acceleration-Discontinuity</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> when there is a step in its </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> motion graph (but there is not a step in the </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Velocity</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Position</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> graphs).</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">A motion is </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">continuous</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> in </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> when there is not a step in its </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Position</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">, </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Velocity</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> motion graphs.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
